The paper deals with the problem of regulating a continuous-time system using neuromorphic vision sensors, which is a topic that falls under the field of robotics (cs.RO). The use of neuromorphic vision sensors also involves computer vision (cs.CV) and signal processing (cs.SY). The paper also presents a controller design, which falls under the field of control theory (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses optimization techniques to design the controller, which is a topic that falls under machine learning (cs.LG).
